Sets up and verifies 10,000 contemporaneous VPN tunnel connections.

DUT is typically a firewall or router.

Intel DPDK is used for raw access to network interface cards.

Network diagram:

 _________________________________
|                                 |
|               DUT               |
|                                 |
| 172.16.0.1/16     172.17.0.1/16 |
| LAN                         WAN |
|_________________________________|
   |                           |
   |                           |
   |                           |
   |                           |
 __|___________________________|__
|                                 |
| LAN_PORT_ID         WAN_PORT_ID |
| 172.16.0.0/16        172.17.0.2 |
|                                 |
|             Server              |
|_________________________________|

The server simulates 10,000 VPN clients connecting to LAN network through WAN interface.

DUT configuration:

Security Policy
     Site to Site
     IKE using Preshared Secret
     foobar
     172.17.0.2
     0.0.0.0

IKE Authentiction
     foobar
     foobar
     Key Identifier: foobar
     Key Identifier: foobar

Local Networks
     Any address

Remote Networks
     foobar (AO defined as 172.18.0.0/16)

IKE (Phase 1) Proposal
     IKEv2 Mode
     Group 2
     AES-128
     SHA1
     28800

Ipsec (Phase 2) Proposal
     ESP
     AES-128
     SHA1
     28800
